The paper deals with predicting runtime distributions of algorithms using machine learning techniques, specifically deep neural networks. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves data analysis and statistical modeling, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with algorithms for SAT solving and AI planning, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL).
